<br>
New servers show up on an average of about once every 3-4 months, and that includes a rash of them that showed up not long after release.  There hasn't been a new one since the RPG one, and isn't likely to be one any time soon.  If anything the trend will be in reverse - fewer servers.<br>
<br>
Be that as it may, it takes less than a week for the dedicated (psycho?) players to get a character over level 50, and to start getting the really nice gear on their characters.  How many months before the effect shown on the spreadsheets starts to take effect?  Once the twinks and gear problem rears its ugly head IT NEVER GOES AWAY.<br>
<br>
In summary: new servers is not an issue that has any basis for complaint.  If you really wanted, you could actually do a spreadsheet that showed where Wizards are actually at a disadvantage many levels vs other casters on new servers, but fine vs melee.  Then that melts away and the melee twinking puts them at a further disadvantage.<br>
<br>
Oh, and Armok, thanks for considering lower levels, but clicky gear isn't the answer, I don't believe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Don't tell anyone, but I'm<br>  a Gnome who worships Brell!!</span><br>  Posts: 872<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 10:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The new server fallacy</span><hr size=1> Yer right, Grimmy. Clicky gear isn't the answer.<br>
